    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi,\n\nAfter searching the NeoVim source code on GitHub for the 'vim.treesitter.start()' command, I found it in the following 'ftplugin' files:\n\n* `runtime/ftplugin/lua.lua`\n* `runtime/ftplugin/help.lua`\n* `runtime/ftplugin/query.lua`\n\nThe automatic activation of Tree-sitter, especially on older devices or devices with limited resources (such as mobile devices, tablets, and Chromebooks), causes a significant delay in opening the editor. (e.g., when opening a large Lua file) Therefore, it would be useful to have a configuration option to disable Tree-sitter.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo provide more flexibility to users, I propose adding a global option to toggle NeoVim's built-in Tree-sitter. This would allow users to choose whether they want to use the built-in functionality or rely entirely on the nvim-treesitter plugin. A simple configuration variable like `vim.g.ts_enable` could be used to control this behavior. \n",
